Tokyo 2039, Japan has fallen under the control of the multinational organization GHQ after the outbreak, in 2029, of an epidemic caused by a virus known as Apocalypse. Shuu Ouma, wielder of "The Power of Kings", has led a rather secluded life at least until his encounter with Gai Tsusugami and Yuzuriha Inori, members of the resistance, thrusts him into the fight against the GHQ.

Dororo, a young orphan thief, meets Hyakkimaru, a powerful ronin. Hyakkimaru's father, a greedy feudal lord, had made a pact with 12 demons, offering his yet-unborn son's body parts in exchange for great power. Thus, Hyakkimaru - who was born without arms, legs, eyes, ears, a nose or a mouth - was abandoned in a river as a baby. Rescued and raised by Dr. Honma, who equips him with artificial limbs and teaches him sword-fighting techniques, Hyakkimaru discovers that each time he slays a demon, a piece of his body is restored. Now, he roams the war-torn countryside in search of demons.

Young Asta was born with no magic ability in a world where magic is everything. In order to prove his strength and keep a promise with his friend, Asta dreams of becoming the greatest mage in the land, the Wizard King! (Source: Viz Media)

In an age when the corners of the world have been scoured for their secrets, only one place remains unexploreda massive cave system known as the Abyss. Those who traverse its endless pits and labyrinth-like tunnels are known as Cave Raiders. A young orphan named Riko dreams of following in her mothers footsteps as a Cave Raider, and when she meets a strange robot when exploring the Abyss, shes one step closer to achieving her goal! (Source: Seven Seas Entertainment) Note: Nominated for the 11th Manga Taishou Awards (2018).
